Tell HN: Searching for videos on Google gives better results than YouTube
text: I don't know why YT's search quality is so poor. If I want to search for something on YT, I'm much better off googling it instead of using YT's search engine (sometimes also appending site:youtube.com to my query). It all seems like a lost opportunity for YT. Then again, maybe it's designed to increase views rather than provide actually useful information to users.

Ask HN: Map services that offer historical tiles?
text:
I have a growing dataset of historical archives that I'd like to project onto a map, but not today's geographical maps. Some of this data goes back hundreds of years. I'd like to avoid plotting something that happened in "New Spain" over modern-day Mexico. Place names just wouldn't make sense.

I'm having a hard time finding tile servers that offer historical geographies. In fact, it would be great to get maps as far back as hundreds of years even if they aren't detailed. It would be great to have the basic approximated country/region borders with the major names around the globe.
